CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1779523627
OL,3,CBurnham says backing him in by-
OL,4,Celection would be 'vote to change
OL,5,CLabour'
OL,7,FBurnham is widely seen as Sir Keir
OL,8,FStarmer's main rival for a leadership
OL,9,Fchallenge, although Burnham's allies
OL,10,Fsuggest that he may not launch a bid
OL,11,Fto lead immediately if he is
OL,12,Fsuccessful in his attempt to return to
OL,13,FWestminster.
OL,15,FUnder Starmer, Labour suffered heavy
OL,16,Flosses in elections in England, Wales
OL,17,Fand Scotland earlier in May,
OL,18,Ftriggering a wave of speculation
OL,19,Faround the prime minister's position.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31003
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F310A1779523627
OL,3,CBurnham says backing him in by-
OL,4,Celection would be 'vote to change
OL,5,CLabour'
OL,7,FIn an apparent criticism of Starmer's
OL,8,Fleadership, Burnham said: "I know my
OL,9,Fown party needs to change. We need to
OL,10,Fbe better than we have been."
OL,12,FBut when pressed by ITV News Political
OL,13,FCorrespondent Harry Horton about the
OL,14,Fgovernment's latest success in
OL,15,Freducing net migration, Burnham
OL,16,Fpraised the government.
OL,18,FHe said: "It's good to see," and went
OL,19,Fon to say, "it's clear that the
OL,20,Fgovernment is moving in the direction".
OL,26,@pD@[OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,311,300,200,140,000,100
